ver’s seat  john f kennedy assassination  oj simpson  lowfloor passenger bus  heavy equipment rental  references historyedit early yearsedit the company was founded by walter l jacobs in  who started a car rental operation in chicago with a dozen model t ford cars in  jacobs sold it to john d hertz who made it a subsidiary of his yellow truck and coach manufacturing company and renamed it hertz driveurself system he sold a controlling interest in the yellow truck and coach manufacturing company and hence also hertz driveurself to general motors in  who then purchased the remaining shares in  hertz arranged for the omnibus corporation which he also owned to purchase the car rental business back from gm in  he sold all the omnibus corporations public transport interests the same year changed its name to the hertz corporation and floated it on the new york stock exchange the following year the hertz corporationedit in  the new corporation bought new york truck leasing company metropolitan distributors in  the hertz corporation became a wholly owned subsidiary of rca but was operated as a separate entity in  hertz joined and was acquired by ual corporation on december   hertz was sold to park ridge corporation which was then owned by ford motor company and members of hertz senior management in  volvo north america corporation invested in park ridge corporation on june   ford issued a notice that hertz would be let loose in an initial public offering on september   it was announced it was to be sold to private equity companies clayton dubilier  rice the carlyle group and merrill lynch global private equity for  billion in cash and debt acquisition the sale was completed on december   this private equity group took hertz public on november   on january   hertz announced the acquisition of used cars dealer british car auctions bca for an undisclosed sum in november  hertz introduced expressrent kiosks at a number of locations this was the first large scale car rental kiosk deployment in the us using a live agent assistant via video chat on january   it was reported that hertz shares had jumped in value by  after the reported purchase of  million shares by billionaire carl icahn in what was believed to be a hostile takeover attempt in response to icahn’s reported share purchase the hertz board reportedly stated that it would issue one preferred share for each current share in what is referred to as a “poison pill” response key executivesedit michel taride in  kathryn v marinello was named president and chief executive officer and a member of the board of directors of the hertz corporation in december  tom kennedy has served as senior executive vice president and chief financial officer since december  he is responsible for all aspects of financial management encompassing treasury tax risk management accounting financial reporting business planning corporate development and corporate policies and procedures tyler best is the executive vice president and chief information officer since january  he oversees the company’s global information technology it functions alexandria marren is the executive vice president north american rental car operations since august  michel taride was appointed executive vice president and president of hertz international ltd in january  taride has managed fleet planning and remarketing functions of hertz international since december  hertz global holdings incedit in april  hertz and dollarthrifty automotive group announced an agreement under which hertz was to acquire dollarthrifty for a purchase price of us per share subject to shareholder approval in a mix of cash and hertz common stock dollarthrifty investors in tulsa oklahoma rejected this us bid from hertz on september   dollarthrifty subsequently announced on october   that it had taken itself off the market because it did not receive any proposals that would pass antitrust review on august   hertz announced for the second time its intention to acquire dollarthrifty subject to ftc approval in this case for us this merger would yield combined annual sales of us the deal was concluded in november  and resulted in a combined  locations in approximately  countries headquarters relocationedit on may   hertz executives alongside florida governor rick scott announced the company would be relocating its worldwide headquarters from park ridge new jersey to estero florida it will be located on the southeast corner of the intersection of williams road and us highway  south tamiami trail though some operations will still occur in its old headquarters in park ridge locationsedit hertz office on the island of marthas vineyard hertz operates in  countries outside the us hertz has companyoperated locations in  countries the rest being franchises as of december update the company had approximately  staffed rental locations in the united states and around  staffed rental locations internationally overland west is the largest hertz licensee in north america operating  car rental and  car sales locations in  states wilford gwilliam purchased the hertz franchise in  he later sold it to devere j sparrow who led the organization until  when he sold it to his soninlaw jerry h petersen jerry grew the business from just a few rental locations and one sales location to what it is today and still serves as the owner president and ceo fleetedit the hertz fleet consists of a wide majority of vehicle manufacturers with the majority being gm products luxury cars are provided by mercedes infiniti and cadillac previously due to hertzs affiliation with ford the rental fleet of most locations consisted of ford and its brands such as mazda volvo mercury and lincoln along with various others mostly korean and japanese as of december update the company has over  cars in the us and a rental fleet in its international operations of over  cars exclusive of its licensees fleet specialty carsedit in  hertz engaged racing and automotive designer carroll shelby to develop an exclusive version of his modified ford mustang one thousand gth mustangs were built and ultimately sold once their rental use had ended however many of them were missing the matching engine some customers would rent the car for a weekend and swap out the highperformance engine with a base version  cu in  l v engine inspections upon return of the rental unit were not common place so nobody found out until the car was due for service by that time there was no way to track down the engine thief the socalled rentaracer program in the lates was available in selected locations and the fleet also included corvettes jaguar xkes and amc amxs in  the th anniversary of the original gth hertz introduced the shelby mustang gth as part of the fun collection at select locations this was followed in  with a convertible version of the gth  saw  chevrolet corvettes badged as zhz available from selected us airports the following year  convertible zhzs joined the fleet both were finished in hertz corporate yellow with a central black stripe in  hertz paired with penske and ford to manufacture speciallymodified blackandyellow  ford mustang gt premium coupes that were individually numbered for their fleets at select us airports all of hertzs us specialty cars featured sirius satellite radio hertzs neverlost navigation system and other features that may not be equipped or at least may cost extra on their standardclass vehicles green collection and electric carsedit hertz launched its green collection in september  with environmentally friendly vehicles including the toyota prius ford fusion buick lacrosse toyota camry and hyundai sonata all feature environmental protection agency epa highway fuel efficiency ratings of  mpg‑us  l km  mpg‑imp or better on the highway in early  hertz launched its global hybrid rental program in conjunction with a  million donation to the national park foundation hertz has an agreement with nissan to bring the nissan leaf electric car to cer