arketing strategies and maximise revenue opportunities primary duties and responsibilities hertz  carsharing productbe a leading member of the hertz  business team representing the marketing and product development function in the european regionformulate and implement the paneuropean marketing strategy for hertz  by influencing key stakeholders in marketing and sales brand crm digital ux… to deliver the key business objectivesinfluence the ecommerce and hertz  technology to deliver major improvements to the hertz  website integration with hertzcom and mobile appsidentify market research needed to support marketing strategies and product developmentcommunicate marketing strategy to country marketing team and act as product champion and brand guardian to ensure coherent product positioning and promotion across all european marketsown the development of paneuropean marketing and sales collateral and other marketing material when appropriateparticipate actively in the launch of hertz  in new markets or the addition of new partners by working closely with the senior director mobility partnershipsbe responsible for the hertz  paneuropean marketing budget new and existing products for the hertz brandsactively keep abreast of market technology innovation and competitor activitiesdevelop an indepth understanding of customer needs customer experience and pain points by analysing internal customer insightsidentify insights gaps and brief consumer research to research team if requiredhelp to generate ideas for new products and services and improvement of existing productsplan develop and execute pilot by managing crossfunctional teams and external partner when relevantwork with brand team to define positioning and communication messages for newupdated productcompile creative brief to develop collateral and other marketing materials with creative teams or agencydefine offline  online communication touch points and work with key stakeholders in marketing  pr  internal communications to ensure cohesive promotion and success of productprovide ongoing analysis of product performance and proposing changes and development if necessaryact as the key point of contact within the business for newupdated productprovide support to country marketing teams for full rollout and act as product guardian to ensure coherent communication across all european marketsoffering operational and administrative support where applicable  what do we need from you educational backgrounda bachelor’s degree or equivalent professional experience years of experience in a marketing role knowledgeknowledge of product management and integrated marketingunderstanding and use of customer insights to implement marketing strategiesproven stakeholder management experienceawareness of different cultural needs within international markets skillsenthusiastic about marketing and customer focusedwell organised with an ability to manage multiple projects in a fastpaced environmentexperience of working with multiple stakeholdersexperience of managing suppliersattention to detailcreative eyeanalytical thinking abilityfluent english other european languages would be an assetadaptable whilst working in a multicultural environment competencieseffective communication skillsdemonstrates initiativeprocess excellenceagility and adaptabilitytrust and integritydrives executionuses insightful judgment in return for your hard work and dedication you will be rewarded with excellent career opportunities training  development a range of benefits and incentives such as canteen gym staff discount programme and many more  if you believe you have the skills and experience required to succeed within this challenging role in an established organisation please apply now apply not ready to apply share with httpwwwjobsnetjobshertzcorporationenusjobunitedkingdommanagerproductdevelopmentjggydgslvy manager product development job snapshot employee type fulltime location uxbridge job type executive experience not specified date posted  about us for more than  years the hertz corporation has been a leader in our field providing professional vehicle and equipment rental services to clients who rely on us to deliver innovative and customerfocused solutions the secret of our success is our worldclass team of employees and our commitment to providing rewarding career paths fostering personal achievement and celebrating our collective success whether you are just starting your career or are an experienced manager searching for new challenges hertz offers a variety of exciting career opportunities if youre motivated energetic and thrive in a fastpaced and everchanging environment we can offer you a rewarding career where no two days are alike our entrepreneurial culture can give you valuable industry insight and onthejob experience in growing a business from the ground up we welcome talented and competitive people and will reward you with outstanding opportunities for personal and professional development we also offer a program of flexible customizable benefits which include medical dental vision coverage life insurance longterm disability flexible spending accounts vacation paid holidays sick days incomesavings plans us savings bonds and tuition reimbursement if you’re looking for a supportive work environment and an exciting future then you should consider the diverse opportunities available at hertz to learn more about our team of professionals join the hertz corporation talent network today what is a talent network talent networks enhance your job search and application process whether you choose to apply or just leave your information we look forward to staying connected with you why join receive alerts with new job opportunities that match your interests share job opportunities through social media or email view all jobs check out our similar jobs business development jobs account manager jobs jobs in crawley west sussex business development jobs in crawley west sussex priva